        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 6:20AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 619 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Ricardo to 7 miles
northeast of Riviera Beach to 16 miles southwest of Malaquite Beach.
Movement was south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kingsville, Riviera Beach, Ricardo, Kingsville Naval Air Station,
Riviera, and Loyola Beach.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 694 and 706.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
